data.content:
noun
[noncount] :the part of a baseball outfield that is to the left when you are looking out from home plate
a fly ball to (deep/shallow) left field also; :the position of the player defending left field
He plays left field.
come out of left field
US informal :to be very surprising and unexpected
That question came out of left field.
out in left field
US informal :very strange or unusual
ideas that are out in left field
Her position is way out in left field.
